$ DOM example: document.documentElement
@ document.documentElement

`document.documentElement` returns a document's root element (in → development/web/browser/layout-engine#browser-rendering-mode[no-quirks mode], that is).
 Thus, in a → development/web/HTML document, it returns its → development/web/HTML/tags/html[`<html>`] element (even if the document does not have an explicit `<html>` element).

